Privacy Policy for ApeStonks

Effective Date: 2024-01-17

1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy governs the collection, use, processing, and disclosure of data collected from users (“Users”) of the ApeStonks mobile application (“App”), developed by Kaeleb Rocha. By using the App, Users consent to the practices described in this document.

2. Data Collection
The App collects data, including user initials for leaderboard purposes, in-app purchase history, and technical data related to app interaction. The App does not link this data to any personal identifier of the User.

3. Use of Data
Collected data is used for:
	•	Display on the leaderboard.
	•	Managing in-app purchases.
	•	Enhancing user experience and App functionality.

4. Anonymization of Data
Data collected and displayed within the App is anonymized. There is no feasible method to associate the data with any specific individual without access to their personal device.

5. Data Retention
Once uploaded to the App, data cannot be deleted, as it is anonymized and unidentifiable. Users should be aware of this permanence before submitting their data.

6. Data Security
We employ industry-standard measures to protect the data collected. However, absolute security cannot be guaranteed.

7. User Rights
Users have the right to access their anonymized data but, due to the nature of the data collection, do not have the right to request its deletion or modification.

8. Third-Party Service Providers
Third-party services engaged by the App are contractually obligated to maintain the confidentiality of the data and are prohibited from using it for any other purpose.

9. Children’s Privacy
The App does not knowingly collect data from children under 13. If it is discovered that such data has been collected, efforts will be made to delete it.

10. Links to External Sites
The App may contain links to other websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external sites.

11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Users will be notified of any significant changes.

12. Governing Law
This Policy shall be governed by the laws of [Jurisdiction], and any disputes relating to it will fall under the jurisdiction of [Jurisdiction’s] courts.

13. Contact Information
For inquiries or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, contact us at cardboardhouse@gmail.com.
